{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QLKZ32Qk3w1VamtzEH6zM2","type":"tool_result","content":"  2700→4. **Cost monitoring should trigger alerts.** If the system had flagged \"68 consecutive sessions with no story state changes,\" a human could have intervened 60 sessions ago.\n  2701→5. **\"Sprint complete\" should be a terminal state.** Once all stories are `done`, Ralph should exit. There is no reason for the orchestrator to keep running.\n  2702→\n  2703→### 7. Action Items\n  2704→\n  2705→| # | Action | Owner | Priority |\n  2706→|---|--------|-------|----------|\n  2707→| 1 | **Kill Ralph immediately** — `kill $(pgrep -f ralph)` or stop the cron/loop | Human | CRITICAL |\n  2708→| 2 | **Nuke stale state** — `rm ralph/.state-snapshot.json` to prevent reoccurrence if Ralph restarts | Human | CRITICAL |\n  2709→| 3 | **Add sprint-complete exit** — Ralph should check `stories_remaining === 0` and exit cleanly | Dev (post-sprint) | High |\n  2710→| 4 | **Make circuit breaker functional** — Ralph must read `.circuit_breaker_state` and respect `OPEN` state | Dev (post-sprint) | High |\n  2711→| 5 | **Add consecutive no-op detection** — if Ralph fixes the same stories N times in a row, halt and alert | Dev (post-sprint) | Medium |\n  2712→| 6 | **Investigate state reversion root cause** — why does Ralph's in-memory state not reflect the completed stories? Is it a snapshot timing issue or a code bug? | Dev (post-sprint) | Medium |\n  2713→| 7 | **Add cost alerting** — flag when no-op session count exceeds a threshold (e.g., 3) | Dev (post-sprint) | Low |\n  2714→\n  2715→### Final Note\n  2716→\n  2717→This retrospective contains no new information. Every section above has been written, in substance, 10+ times across previous retros in this file. The only number that changes is the session count and the total spend. The problem is fully diagnosed. The fix is trivial (kill the process). The blocker is human action.\n  2718→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013EiYxqV7gKFat56QSc1gyT","session_id":"ba9b6441-b0e3-4dcb-9af8-be1fd0c76b67","uuid":"56f38110-7d7f-4758-b6eb-d2d20b95b61f","timestamp":"2026-03-28T07:06:27.403Z"}
